main event: A naval vessel detected an object with starlike characteristics but moving at great speed overhead.
interesting points: The object was detected at a high altitude and was moving very rapidly.
The object passed rapidly overhead at a great height, with an initial bearing of 205-215 degrees (true) and a distance of 30-40 miles.
The visibility was clear, with 5 point seas and 5/10 cloud coverage.
The report was classified as MERIT-UFO, suggesting it was considered a potentially unidentified flying object.
The report was sent to various naval and military organizations, including the Defense Intelligence Agency (DIA).
sighted object: an object with starlike characteristics but moving at great speed
